Gohi

Introduction

Vanillare (바닐레어) is a South Korean pop/rock band formed in 2019 by singer-songwriter Gohi. Debuting as a duo with drummer Ji Yong-hee in 2021, they released their first EP, “Hollywood Fever.” After Ji Yong-hee‘s departure in 2023, Gohi continued the project with guest musicians called “Good Hands.” Known for blending pop, rock, and emo influences, their discography includes singles like “Remedy” and the album “Smoking with the Angel.” Vanillare engages fans through social media and remains committed to creating diverse, resonant music.

On February 7, 2025, Gohi announced their transition to a solo career, with all future releases and performances under their name. Their bandmates will continue supporting them as the session band Vanillare, performing together as Gohi with Vanillare. Past music will also be rebranded under Gohi after the release of their next single album.
